Subject:    Authority for inverse domains
From:       <a href="?a=95837786600040&r=1&w=2">news () psuvax1 ! cs ! psu ! edu  (Daniel Ehrlich)</a>
Date:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2&b=198912">1989-12-19 19:40:50</a></font>
[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837784627097&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837784627097&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

Another question for the BIND Gurus to ponder.  We (Penn State) are in the
process of setting up individual domain servers for each sub-domain, so they
can be locally adminstered by the department that owns the equipment.
Splitting up the name to address files works fine.  The question that has
come up is "Can we do the same for the inverse domain (address -&gt; name)
files and expect it to work correctly?"

Has anyone else done this?  I would like to hear what your solution was.
Thanks in advance.

--
